Pimentón de La Vera is paprika from Spain's western region of Extremadura, traditionally used to season sausages and other cured meats. It is produced from mature red peppers, which are dried and smoked over oak fires, then ground to a uniquely smooth, almost talc-like texture. It is the first aromatic seasoning to acquire the coveted status of a ''denominación de origen'' (denomination of origin).